        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(channels): stop duplicating inbound previews in system events",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Fixes a prompt-context duplication bug where Slack and Microsoft Teams inbound handlers copied a 160-character user-message preview into queued `System:` events even though the full user body is already delivered through the normal inbound context.\r\n- This matters now because #94549 shows the issue still reproduces on recent OpenClaw releases: long Slack/Teams messages can appear truncated in model-visible system-event text, making the model think the user message was cut off.\r\n- The intended outcome is notification-only system events such as `Slack DM from Alice` / `Teams message in channel from Member`, while the full message remains available through `BodyForAgent` and the existing channel history/body paths.\r\n- Out of scope: changing system-event formatting globally, changing channel history behavior, changing reaction/thread-parent system events, or adding live Slack/Teams transport behavior.\r\n- Success looks like Slack and Teams no longer duplicate inbound body text in system-event labels, with focused regression coverage proving the body still reaches the agent path.\r\n- Reviewers should focus on the two enqueue call sites and the updated regression assertions in `extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts` and `extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts`.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\n\r\nCloses #94549\r\n\r\nRelated #67503\r\nRelated #67761\r\nRelated #93966\r\nRelated #12850\nRelated #88261\n\n## Maintainer refresh\n\n- Rebased onto current `main` at `fcec95ffd7a589d2b1a3af646bba2de371c67e97`.\n- Focused regression proof rerun: Mattermost 10 tests, Teams 18 tests, Slack 85 tests; all passed.\n- Fresh branch autoreview: no actionable findings; correctness confidence 0.98.\n- Linux changed type/lint/guard lanes passed on Azure Crabbox run `run_ac01a2c3b8f1`, lease `cbx_c269deaeb84e` (stopped).\n\r\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\r\n\r\nNo. I selected this from the public issue queue after ClawSweeper marked it source-reproducible, queueable, and clear in fix shape.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Slack and Microsoft Teams inbound message handlers were enqueueing user-authored body previews into model-visible system events, causing duplicate and sometimes truncated copies of the user's message to appear before the full body.\r\n- Real environment tested: macOS local OpenClaw source checkout on branch `codex/fix-94549-inbound-system-preview`, Node v22.22.0.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts\r\ngit diff --check\r\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts\r\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts\r\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Evidence after fix:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.extension-mattermost.config.ts\r\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\r\nTests  10 passed (10)\r\n\r\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.extension-msteams.config.ts\r\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\r\nTests  18 passed (18)\r\n\r\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.extension-slack.config.ts\r\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\r\nTests  85 passed (85)\r\n\r\n[test] passed 3 Vitest shards in 44.73s\r\n\r\nChecking formatting...\r\nAll matched files use the correct format.\r\n\r\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\r\noverall: patch is correct (0.82)\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Observed result after fix: The Slack regression now expects `enqueueSystemEvent(\"Slack DM from Alice\", ...)` while separately asserting the full body still appears in `BodyForAgent`. The Teams regressions now find `Teams message in channel from Member` system events and assert the inbound body text is absent from the system-event label while still present in the dispatched `BodyForAgent`.\r\n- What was not tested: Live Slack or Microsoft Teams delivery against real workspace/tenant credentials.\r\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The focused proof exercises the production Slack `prepareSlackMessage` and Microsoft Teams `createMSTeamsMessageHandler` paths through OpenClaw's extension test harness with mocked Slack/Teams transport and runtime boundaries. It proves the prompt-context construction behavior under this patch, but it is not a live provider/channel end-to-end run.\r\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Before this change, Slack enqueued `${inboundLabel}: ${preview}` in `extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts`, and Teams enqueued the same `${inboundLabel}: ${preview}` shape in `extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.ts`. Reverting those two production-line changes makes the updated label-only regression assertions fail because the system-event text again contains the user body preview.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n\r\nCommands run:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts\r\ngit diff --check\r\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts\r\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts\r\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\r\n```\r\n\r\nRegression coverage added or updated:\r\n\r\n- Updated Slack prepare coverage to assert the queued inbound system event does not include body text while `BodyForAgent` retains the full message.\r\n- Updated Teams authz coverage for both skipped and dispatched channel messages to assert the primary system event remains owner-neutral and body-free, while dispatched messages still carry the full `BodyForAgent`.\r\n- Ran Mattermost inbound system-event tests as sibling proof that the already-correct regular-post behavior remains green.\r\n\r\nWhat failed before this fix:\r\n\r\n- The updated Slack and Teams label-only assertions fail on the old code path because the queued system-event text includes `: ${preview}` from the user body.\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n\r\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\r\n\r\nYes. Model-visible channel context changes for Slack and Microsoft Teams inbound messages: duplicate/truncated body previews are removed from `System:` event text.\r\n\r\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\r\n\r\nNo.\r\n\r\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\r\n\r\nNo.\r\n\r\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\r\n\r\nPrompt/context semantics for Slack and Microsoft Teams inbound turns.\r\n\r\nHow is that risk mitigated?\r\n\r\nThe change is limited to the system-event label string. Session keys, context keys, routing, history recording, debug previews, and the normal full-body delivery path are preserved. Focused regression tests cover both removed duplication and retained `BodyForAgent` content.\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\n\r\nWhat is the next action?\r\n\r\nFresh CI is running on the rebased head.\n\r\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\r\n\r\nLive Slack/Teams tenant proof was not run locally; focused source-checkout proof covers the production handler paths, and the broad changed gate passed on Linux.\n\r\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\r\n\r\nFresh branch autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings at 0.98 correctness confidence.\n\r\nAI-assisted (Codex). Human-run local validation is recorded above.\r\n",
